# Internationalization (i18n) Rules

## CRITICAL: No Hardcoded Strings

All user-facing text MUST be translated. Never hardcode strings in components.

```vue
<!-- ❌ FORBIDDEN - Hardcoded strings -->
<button>Save</button>
<p>Loading...</p>
<h1>Welcome to My Resume App</h1>
<span>Error: Something went wrong</span>

<!-- ✅ CORRECT - Use translations -->
<script setup lang="ts">
import { useI18n } from '@/i18n'
const { t } = useI18n()
</script>

<template>
  <button>{{ t('common.save') }}</button>
  <p>{{ t('common.loading') }}</p>
  <h1>{{ t('home.welcome') }}</h1>
  <span>{{ t('errors.somethingWentWrong') }}</span>
</template>
```

