## Using Translations

### Basic Usage

```vue
<script setup lang="ts">
import { useI18n } from '@/i18n'

const { t, locale, isRtl, setLocale } = useI18n()
</script>

<template>
  <div :dir="isRtl ? 'rtl' : 'ltr'">
    <h1>{{ t('nav.home') }}</h1>
    <button @click="setLocale('ar')">العربية</button>
    <button @click="setLocale('en')">English</button>
  </div>
</template>
```

### With Interpolation

```typescript
// In translation file
export default {
  greeting: 'Hello, {name}!',
  items: 'You have {count} items'
}

// In component
t('greeting', { name: user.name })  // "Hello, John!"
t('items', { count: 5 })            // "You have 5 items"
```

### Nested Keys

```typescript
// Access nested keys with dot notation
t('auth.login')         // "Log in"
t('resume.workExperience')  // "Work Experience"
t('errors.required')    // "This field is required"
```

## Adding New Translations

1. Add the key to `src/i18n/en.ts`
2. Add the Arabic translation to `src/i18n/ar.ts`
3. Use dot notation for organization

```typescript
// Step 1: Add to en.ts
export default {
  // ... existing
  myFeature: {
    title: 'My Feature Title',
    description: 'This is the description'
  }
}

// Step 2: Add to ar.ts
export default {
  // ... existing
  myFeature: {
    title: 'عنوان الميزة',
    description: 'هذا هو الوصف'
  }
}

// Step 3: Use in component
t('myFeature.title')
t('myFeature.description')
```

## RTL Support

### Conditional Classes

```vue
<template>
  <!-- Using isRtl -->
  <div :class="{ 'text-right': isRtl, 'text-left': !isRtl }">
    Content
  </div>

  <!-- Using Tailwind RTL utilities -->
  <div class="text-left rtl:text-right mr-4 rtl:mr-0 rtl:ml-4">
    Content
  </div>

  <!-- Using logical properties (preferred) -->
  <div class="text-start ms-4 me-2">
    Content
  </div>
</template>
```

### Icons and Arrows

```vue
<!-- Flip icons in RTL -->
<ChevronRightIcon :class="{ 'rotate-180': isRtl }" />

<!-- Or use CSS -->
<span class="rtl:rotate-180">→</span>
```

## Common Patterns

### Form Labels

```vue
<label class="block text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
  {{ t('auth.email') }}
</label>
<input type="email" :placeholder="t('auth.email')" />
```

### Error Messages

```vue
<span v-if="error" class="text-red-500 text-sm">
  {{ t(`errors.${error}`) }}
</span>

<!-- Or with fallback -->
<span v-if="error" class="text-red-500 text-sm">
  {{ t(`errors.${error}`, t('errors.somethingWentWrong')) }}
</span>
```

### Dynamic Content

```vue
<template>
  <p>
    {{ t('resume.sectionCount', { count: sections.length }) }}
  </p>
</template>
```

## Translation Keys Checklist

When adding new features, ensure translations for:
- [ ] Page titles
- [ ] Button labels
- [ ] Form labels and placeholders
- [ ] Error messages
- [ ] Success messages
- [ ] Empty state messages
- [ ] Confirmation dialogs
- [ ] Tooltips
- [ ] Navigation items
